# Run tests before committing

Before creating any git commit in this project:

1. Run tests locally first — use whichever works on the machine:
   - `./scripts/test.sh` (Git Bash / macOS / Linux)
   - `.\scripts\test.ps1` (PowerShell)
   - `scripts\test.bat` (CMD)
   - `npm test` (only if npm is on PATH)
2. Only commit if all 20 tests pass.
3. If tests fail, fix them first — do not commit broken code.
4. Do not rely on GitHub Actions as the first check; local tests must pass first.

Install git hooks once: `./scripts/setup-hooks.sh` or `.\scripts\setup-hooks.ps1`
